@startuml
[*] --> StartState: start date arrives
note right of StartState
The system shall keep the rate in a waiting state until the start date arrives.
end note
StartState --> ActiveState: current date equals or surpasses its start date
note right of ActiveState
The system shall activate the rate once the current date equals or surpasses its start date.
end note
ActiveState --> ActiveState: validity period not ended
note right of ActiveState
The system shall maintain the rate's active state until the end of its validity period.
end note
ActiveState --> ExpiredState: finish date is reached
note right of ExpiredState
The system shall mark the rate as expired once the finish date is reached.
end note
ExpiredState --> RemovedState: one year from expiration date
note right of RemovedState
The system shall remove or archive the rate after one year from its expiration date.
end note
@enduml
